Mesenteries and internal anatomy: Two siphonoglyphs visible in most specimens; actinopharynx ribbed, darker beige than column. Mesenteries to five orders (Figure 4a); 
thin
, each with oral but no marginal stoma. Retractor muscles diffuse (Figure 4b). Parietobasilar muscle with short free penon. Sexes presumably separate: three females, one male examined. First three orders complete and sterile, rest incomplete and fertile (Figure 4a).
